    <sTitle>Thermodynamic characteristics of reactions with KH(PO3H)</sTitle>
    <sAbstract>The standard formation enthalpy of KH(PO3H) has been determined by solution calorimetry  combining the solution enthalpies of KH(PO3H) and KOH + H3PO3 mixtures in 2 M HCl at 298.15 K and  literature data for the first time. It has been obtained that above-mentioned compound is  thermodynamically stable with respect to their decomposition into binary oxides at room  temperatures. It has been established that KH(PO3H) does not react with water and CO2 at ambient  temperatures.</sAbstract>
